      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAR DAN BUDDY (9) has been racing well in strong company this time in, highlighted a G3 win in Victoria and a Kilmore Cup placing when only 4m behind Leap To Fame. Only beaten 2m into third the G2 Light Horse FFA at Menangle last start. He is two from two at this circuit and looks hard to stop. MY ULTIMATE BARNEY (7) draws wide but was good when beaten just over a metre into second at his most recent outing at Melton and placed behind flying mare Captains Mistress at Listed level in Sydney last month. Goes very well at this distance with three wins and two placings from six attempts and won the only time he raced here. SOHO GUNSLINGER (4) enjoyed the class drop from the Chariots of Fire when he raced three wide without cover before landing a last-start win by 6 metres at Menangle and he draw closer to the pegs.. SANCHEZ (1) is ticking along well with placings in his last three starts, two of them from this barrier including a 1.2m second in the G3 4YO Bonanza.",
